n```\n\nNow `h1 i` gives `Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y` for any `i`. Now we need to show that `x = y` in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h2 : x = y := by\n```\n\nTo show `x = y`, we need to show `x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h3 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, x Ôëí y [ZMOD (I i)] := by\n  intro i\n```\n\nNow we need to show `x Ôëí y [ZMOD (I i)]` for all `i`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y := h1 i\n```\n\nFrom `h4`, we have `Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y`. By the definition of congruence in the quotient, this means `x Ôëí y [ZMOD (I i)]`.\n\n```tactics\nexact Quotient.eq_iff_eq.mp h4\n```\n\nNow we have `h3 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, x Ôëí y [ZMOD (I i)]`. We need to show `x = y` in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h4 : x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i := by\n  simp only [mem_iInter]\n  exact fun i => by\n    have h5 : x Ôëí y [ZMOD (I i)] := h3 i\n    exact h5\n```\n\nNow we have `h4 : x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i`. This means `x` and `y` are in the same equivalence class in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`, so `x = y`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h5 : x = y := by\n  have h6 : x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i := h4\n  simp only [mem_iInter] at h6\n  all_goals\n    try { tauto }\n    try { \n      have h7 : x - y Ôłł I i := h6 i\n      have h8 : x - y Ôłł I i := h7\n      tauto\n    }\n```\n\nWait, this approach is getting complicated. Let's think more directly. `h4 : x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i` means `ÔłÇ i, x - y Ôłł I i`. But in the quotient `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`, the equality `x = y` is defined as `x - y Ôłł ÔĘů i, I i`.\n\n```tactics\nexact h5\n```\n\nWait, we need to properly complete the proof. Let's fix the structure.\n\n```tactics\nintro x y h\n```\n\nNow `h : chineseMap I x = chineseMap I y`. We need to show `x = y`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h1 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y := by\n  simpa using congr_fun h\n```\n\nNow `h1 i` gives `Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y` for any `i`. Now we need to show that `x = y` in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i