variable {╬╣ : Type} (I : ╬╣ Ôćĺ Ideal R)

/-
We want to create a ring homomorphism from the quotient of `R` by the intersections of the `I i`ÔÇÖs
to the product of the quotients `RÔžŞ(I i)`.
For every `i : ╬╣` we have a homomorphism from `R` to `RÔžŞ(I i)`, namely `Quotient.mk (I i)`.
Gathering all those in a map from `R` to the products `╬á i, (R ÔžŞ I i)` is a job for
`Pi.ringHom`. We will need the lemma `ker_Pi_Quotient_mk` about this `Pi.ringHom`.
And then we need `Ideal.lift` to factors this through the quotient of `R` by the intersection
`ÔĘů i, I i`. Be careful that, depending on the font you are using, the intersection symbol `ÔĘů` and the
product `╬á` could be tricky to distinguish.
-/

def chineseMap  : (R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i) Ôćĺ+* ╬á i, R ÔžŞ I i :=
  Quotient.lift (ÔĘů i, I i) (Pi.ringHom fun i : ╬╣ ÔćŽ Quotient.mk (I i))
    (by sorry)

