Actually, `Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y` implies `x - y Ôłł I i`.

The definition of `Quotient.mk` is such that `Quotient.mk a = Quotient.mk b` if and only if `a - b Ôłł I`.

So, `Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y` directly implies `x - y Ôłł I i`.

Let's fix the previous step:

```tactics
have h2 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, x - y Ôłł I i := by
  intro i
  have h3 : Quotient.mk (I i) x = Quotient.mk (I i) y := h1 i
  have : x - y Ôłł I i := by
    have h4 : (x : R) - (y : R) Ôłł I i := by
      exact Quotient.eq_zero_iff_mem.mp (show Quotient.mk (I i) x - Quotient.mk (I i) y = 0 by rw [h3]; simp)
    exact h4
  assumption
```

Now, we have that for all `i : ╬╣`, `x - y Ôłł I i`. This means `x - y` is in the intersection `ÔĘů i, I i`.

```tactics
