```

We have that for all `i : ╬╣`, `Quotient.mk (I i) (x i) = Quotient.mk (I i) (y i)`. From this, we need to show `x = y` in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`.

To show `x = y` in the quotient, we need to show that for all `i : ╬╣`, `x i = y i` in `R`. 

```tactics
have h2 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, x i = y i := by
  intro i
  have h3 : Quotient.mk (I i) (x i) = Quotient.mk (I i) (y i) := h1 i
```

From `h3`, we have `Quotient.mk (I i) (x i) = Quotient.mk (I i) (y i)`. The map `Quotient.mk (I i)` is injective because `I i` is an ideal, so this implies `x i = y i`.

```tactics
have h4 : x i = y i := by
  exact Quotient.mk_inj (I i) h3
exact h4
```

Now that we have `h2 : ÔłÇ i : ╬╣, x i = y i`, we can show that `x = y` in `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i`.

```tactics
exact Quotient.injOn (fun i => h2 i)
```

The proof is now complete. We have shown that if `x` and `y` are elements of `R ÔžŞ ÔĘů i, I i` such that `chineseMap I x = chineseMap I y`, then `x = y`. This proves that `chineseMap I` is injective.
